cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the problem of temporal action detection in videos, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and investigates input feature types and fusion strategies, which are related to machine learning and deep learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on two datasets and compares it with state-of-the-art systems, which involves performance analysis and evaluation metrics, indicating a possible fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
